videos.description: Mountaineers QB Taylor Lamb uses his legs for a 32-yard pickup.
videos.headline: Lamb breaks free for big App State gain

videos.description: The Bulldogs strike first as Nick Chubb converts at the goal line.
videos.headline: Chubb pounds it in for first Georgia TD of season

videos.description: Sony Michel finds a big hole and rushes 44 yards on third down.
videos.headline: Michel bursts out of the backfield to extend Bulldog drive

videos.description: Javon Wims makes a catch between multiple defenders and extends the ball out to cross the goal line.
videos.headline: Georgia's Wims stretches out to find end zone

videos.description: Appalachian State's Ike Lewis leaps up and makes a great one-handed catch for 28 yards.
videos.headline: Lewis makes sick one-handed grab

videos.description: Jake Fromm lofts one up to D'Andre Swift who makes a nifty one-hand grab to extend Georgia's drive.
videos.headline: Swift only needs one hand to convert Bulldog 1st Down

videos.description: Sony Michel runs through multiple Mountaineers en route to a 6-yard touchdown run.
videos.headline: Michel bowls over defenders for Georgia TD

videos.description: After an injury to the starting quarterback, Georgia Head Coach Kirby Smart says he's pleased with the play of his freshman backup Jake Fromm.
videos.headline: Coach Smart impressed with Freshman QB

videos.description: Freshman QB Jake Fromm finds Javon Wims on fourth down for a 22-yard gain.
videos.headline: Fromm connects with Wims for Bulldogs 4th Down conversion

videos.description: Nick Chubb runs through more Appalachian State defenders for an 8-yard touchdown run.
videos.headline: Chubb finds end zone for second TD of the day

videos.description: Desmond Franklin jumps the receiver's route to intercept Georgia's pass.
videos.headline: Mountaineers' Franklin picks off pass

videos.description: Quarterback Taylor Lamb scrambles on third down and reaches the end zone on a 20-yard run.
videos.headline: Lamb's 20-yard scamper puts App State on the board

videos.description: Nick Chubb rushes for 96 yards and two touchdowns and Georgia cruises to a 31-10 win over Appalachian State despite losing Jacob Eason to injury.
videos.headline: Chubb leads Georgia past Appalachian State
